  "base_commit": "02e3f00370557dda38a94c15ca542e38e5ce1f7a",
  "pr_number": 6174,
  "issue_number": 6166,
  "issue_title": "Support 100 shorthand option for pattern based coverage rules",
  "issue_body": "### Clear and concise description of the problem\n\nAs documented [here](https://vitest.dev/config/#coverage-thresholds-100), we can use this:\r\n```typescript\r\ncoverage: {\r\n    thresholds: {\r\n        '100': true,\r\n    },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis I find to be very useful instead of typing out all of the options with the same value.\r\nThis is however, not supported for pattern based thresholds, where, I would argue, it becomes even more useful.\n\n### Suggested solution\n\nAllow `'100': true` in pattern based coverage tresholds:\r\n\r\n```typescript\r\ncoverage: {\r\n    thresholds: {\r\n        lines: 50,\r\n        function: 70,\r\n\r\n        'src/path1/**/*': { '100': true },\r\n        'src/path2/**/*': { '100': true },\r\n        'src/path3/**/*': { '100': true },\r\n        'src/path4/**/*': { '100': true },\r\n        'src/path5/**/*': { '100': true },\r\n    },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis reduces clutter far more than only allowing this for the global threshold config.\n\n### Alternative\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n\n### Validations\n\n- [X] Follow our [Code of Conduct](https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md)\n- [X] Read the [Contributing Guidelines](https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n- [X] Read the [docs](https://vitest.dev/guide/).\n- [X] Check that there isn't already an issue that request the same feature to avoid creating a duplicate.",
  "merged_at": "2024-07-21T14:20:00Z",
